data.text:
2006-07 (Sophomore)

Played in 30 of 31 games listed 23 times in the starting lineup... Scored a season-high 14 points (6-for-7 FG, 2-for-3 FT) in home games vs. East Tennessee State... Scored 10 points in back to back games vs. Palm Beach Atlantic at home and in Tampa against South Florida... Fifth on the team in rebounding at 3.1 per game... Was a perfect 4-for-4 from the floor and 1-for1 from the 3-point arc in home game vs. Florida State.

2005-06

Sat out entire season as a transfer.

2004-05 (Marshall University)

Played in 11 games as a freshman at Marshall University ... Scored one point (vs. Bowling Green) and collected five rebounds on the season ... Averaged 3.3 minutes per game ... Collected two rebounds vs. East Tennessee State and one rebound each vs. UNC Wilmington, Illinois State, and Xavier.

High School

Played one season at Countryside High School in Clearwater, Fla. ... Led his team in blocked shots ... Had his season cut short due to shoulder surgery ... Played on the Nigerian National team from 2001-03 ... Was a five-time student of the month at Countryside.
